{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015vQuxjuFVUiEq6gmqeH4XR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Changes to `/workspaces/skills/layout-inspecting/scripts/inspect_layout.js`:**\n\n1. **Auto-install bootstrap** — Extended `ensureDependencies()` to auto-install the `canvas` npm package into the skill's own `node_modules/` on first use.\n\n2. **Argument parser** — Added `--save-image <path>` option (stored as `opts.saveImage`), updated help text, and removed the old `--tui`/`--output` incompatibility check.\n\n3. **`renderImage()` function** — New function that:\n   - Scales the layout to fit within 1200×900px while preserving aspect ratio\n   - Creates a node-canvas canvas of the scaled dimensions\n   - Flattens the layout tree in DFS pre-order (parents before children)\n   - Draws each node as a filled rectangle using its `background` color\n   - Draws a border stroke if the node has a `border` property\n   - Overlays label text in a contrasting (black/white) color, clipped to the box\n   - Outputs `.png` or `.jpg`/`.jpeg` based on the file extension\n\n4. **`main()` flow** — All three flags (`--output`, `--save-image`, `--tui`) are now independent and can coexist: JSON is written if `--output` is set, the image is saved if `--save-image` is set, and the TUI launches last if `--tui` is set.\n\n**Verification:** Generated `/tmp/layout.png` (1200×750, valid PNG) from `https://news.ycombinator.com`. Also verified JPG output and concurrent `--output`+`--save-image` usage with `example.com`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":211,"cache_read_input_tokens":43539,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":211},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"